    "Together, these steps collectively help to identify and filter out low-quality data points, such as those with hallucination issues or inaccurate argument parameter values.",
    "For supervised fine-tuning (SFT), our dataset combines training samples from three main sources: cleaned and augmented agent datasets, a synthetic function-calling dataset, and general instructiontuning datasets.",
    "These sources are used to train the general xLAM models.",
    "Specifically, to enhance the general instruction capability of xLAM, we integrate diverse instruction-tuning datasets from DialogStudio (Zhang et al., 2023) and Data Provenance (Longpre et al., 2023 (Longpre et al.,, 2024)).",
    "This instruction data comprises 20% to 30% of our training set."
